<title>September 25, 1996 Press Release</title>

<body>

<font size=-1>

FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE<br>
September 25, 1996<br>
CONTACT: Kristi S. Hamrick -- (202) 393-2100. For Radio: Kristin Hansen.
</font>

<p>

<center><h2>Media Advisory:

<p>

A WHO'S WHO OF FAITH AND FAMILY<br>
LEADERS TO SPEAK FOR LIFE</h2>

<p>

<h4>FOLLOWING PRAYER BREAKFAST, NEWS CONFERENCE ON<br>
PARTIAL BIRTH ABORTION TO BE HELD IN U.S. CAPITOL.<br>
(Senate expected to attempt veto override Thursday.)</h4></center>

<p>

<center><h4><u>WHEN: Thursday, Sept. 26<br>
TIME: 10 a.m. to 11 a.m.<br>
WHERE: S-211, LBJ Room

<p>

WHO:</u><br>
Dr. James Dobson, Focus on the Family<br>
Gary Bauer, Family Research Council<br>
Charles Colson, Prison Fellowship<br>
Pat Robertson, Christian Broadcasting Network<br>
Richard Land, Christian Life Commission of the Southern Baptist 
Convention<br>
Beverly LaHaye, Concerned Women for America<br>
Adrian Rogers, Southern Baptist Convention<br>
Father Richard John Neuhaus, editor <i>First Things</i><br>
Wanda Franz, National Right to Life<br>
Paul Weyrich, Free Congress<br>
Bob Dugan, National Association of Evangelicals

<p>

And to be announced:<br>
U.S. Leaders of the Catholic Church

<p>

ALSO NOTE:<br>
Pro-family, faith and life leaders will
be available to react to the life vote. More information available
closer to event.</h4></center>

