<title>July 10, 1996 Press Release</title>

<body>

<font size=-1>

FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE<br>
July 10, 1996<br>
CONTACT: Kristi S. Hamrick -- (202) 393-2100. For Radio: Kristin Hansen.
</font>

<p>

<center><h4>** MEDIA ADVISORY **</h4>
<h2>FRC TO TESTIFY ON CAPITOL HILL...</h2></center>

<p>

<li><h4>GARY BAUER ON THE DEFENSE OF MARRIAGE ACT</h4>

<p>

On <B>Thursday, July 11</B> at <B>10:00 AM</B>, Family
Research Council President Gary Bauer will testify before the
Senate Judiciary Committee in support of the Defense of Marriage
Act (S. 1740). The hearing will take place in the <B>Senate Dirksen
Building, Room 226</B>.

<p>

&quot;This is by far one of the most crucial pieces
of legislation ever to be voted on in Congress,&quot; Bauer said
Wednesday. &quot;This bill was not invented to oppress a segment
of our society, but rather to defend the institution of marriage
- the core of our civilization - from being redefined into oblivion.&quot;

<p>

The House of Representatives is tentatively scheduled
to vote on DOMA (H.R. 3396) on Friday, July 12.

<p>

<li><h4>GRACIE HSU ON ABSTINENCE</h4>

<p>

Also on <B>Thursday</B> at <B>9:30 a.m.,</B> FRC
Policy Analyst Gracie Hsu will testify before the Senate Appropriations
Subcommittee on the funding for abstinence programs in Title XX.
The hearing will take place in the <B>Senate Dirksen Building,
Room 138.</B>

<p>

<center><h4>FOR A COPY OF TESTIMONY, MORE INFORMATION, OR INTERVIEWS,<br>
CONTACT THE FRC MEDIA OFFICE AT (202) 393-2100.</h4></center>

