<html>

<title>Daily Commentary - December 5, 1996</title>

<body>

<center><h1>Daily Commentary<br>
December 5, 1996</h1></center>

<p><hr width=75% size=3><p>

I'm Gary Bauer for Washington Watch.

<p>

The year's not over yet, but here's my award for most cynical:
Those liberals in Congress and out who denounced the Defense of
Marriage Act.  &quot;It's years away,&quot; they said of homosexual
marriage. &quot;Nobody's legalizing this,&quot; they said.  Conservatives
are &quot;jumping the gun,&quot; they charged.

<p>

Guess what. Hawaii's Supreme Court has just ruled that gay marriage
is legal in the Aloha State.  Pro-gay Bill Clinton has been safely
re-elected.  And the same people who denounced the Defense of
Marriage Act have forgotten everything they said just a few months
ago.  Then, Clinton's spokeswoman said he &quot;scorned&quot;
the Defense of Marriage bill -- even as he signed it. And the
press sure scorned it.

<p>

But events in Hawaii prove how timely, how important, how <I>needed</I> 
the Defense of Marriage Act was.  This fight is not over.
We will not give in.  The overwhelming majority of people in
America -- and in Hawaii itself -- <I>oppose</I> homosexual marriage.
The more people find out about it, the more strongly they want
to defend true marriage. Remember, what the radical homosexuals
really want is not marriage for them, but the <I>end</I> of marriage
for everyone.

<p>

For Family Research Council, this is Gary Bauer with today's
Washington Watch.  For more information about us, call 1-800-225-4008.
That number again:  1-800-225-4008.

<p>

