<title>Daily Commentary - January 9, 1997</title>

<body>

<center><h1>Daily Commentary<br>
January 9, 1997</h1></center>

<p><hr width=75% size=3><p>

I'm Gary Bauer for Washington Watch.

<p>

Vice President Al Gore will celebrate the twenty-fourth anniversary
of <I>Roe v. Wade </I>on January 22nd.  That's right, I said <I>celebrate.</I> 
He will be the keynote speaker at a gala luncheon sponsored
by NARAL, the militant National Abortion Rights Action League.
Gore will appear with actress Demi Moore.

<p>

Tipper Gore, the Vice President's wife, will present a <I>lifetime</I> 
achievement award.  Sad that Tipper honors some <I>lifetimes</I>
while millions are snuffed out.

<p>

NARAL, of course, presses for abortion-on-demand with American
taxpayers paying for it.  They defend every one of the 30 million
abortions that have been performed since 1973.

<p>

How tragic for Al and Tipper Gore.  Just eleven years ago,
<I>Senator</I> Al Gore wrote of his <I>deep, personal conviction
that abortion is wrong.</I> Today the Gores chose to be honored
by the abortion lobby.

<p>

It is always sad when someone aboandons principle for political
gain.  But time and time again, our unborn children have been
abandoned by politicians.  And that is a tragedy.

<p>

For Family Research Council, this is Gary Bauer with today's
Washington Watch.  For more information about us, call 1-800-225-4008.
That number again:  1-800-225-4008.

<p>

