<P><center>
<H2>Ivory Towering Inferno</H2>
</CENTER>
<P>
<blockquote>
	"The Young America's Foundation of Herndon, Va., has published 'Comedy and tragedy,' a list of some of the courses available at the nation's institutions of higher learning. . . .
<P>
	"Not surprisingly, some of the course descriptions that standout, even in this amazing list, come from the University of Massachusetts at Amherst, locally called Zoo Mass, where the education department offers three different courses on 'Special Issues in Education,' including two fairly recent concerns of the left, 'Handicapism—Dynamics of Handicapism on Personal and Institutional Levels,' 'Heterosexism—Dynamics of Heterosexism on Personal and Institutional Levels,' and third, that timeworn leftist obsession, 'Classism—Dynamics of Classism on Personal and Institutional Levels.'
<P>
	"But from the University of California at Santa Cruz comes the scariest offering. A Big Brother—or should we say, Big Sister-minded education department presents students with Education 189: 'Monitoring Girls for Science and Math Equity: This six-credit, multiple-term course provides opportunities for women students from any discipline to mentor girls in local K–12 classrooms. Mentors are trained to promote equity in science, math, and technology.' Gifted boys had better learn to keep quiet or face fierce reprimand."
<P>
—Stephen Goode, <I>Insight</I>, October 28, 1996

</blockquote>
<!------------------------------------------------------------>
<P>
