<h3>Resource Bank</h3><p>
From the September Edition of <i>The Insider</i><br>

<h2>Of Note</h2><p>
</center>
<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=2>Mackinac Center Offers Freedom From Bad Labor
Advice</FONT></B>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Times New Roman">This resource from the Mackinac
Center gives workers straight answers to common questions about
labor unions and employee rights and responsibilities. The question-and-answer
format helps workers understand how federal labor law affects
them directly on topics including mandatory union membership and
payment dues. Public employees, including teachers, will also
benefit from this brochure.  CONTACT: Mackinac Center for Public
Policy, 119 Ashman Street, P.O. Box 568, Midland, MI 48640, 517/631-0900,
fax 517/631-0964. <BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=2>Fund to Take Back Texas Prisons, Inc. Established</FONT></B>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Times New Roman">The Fund to Take Back Texas
Prisons, Inc., has been created to end the Federal Judiciary's
contol over Texas prisons by restoring state sovereignty for Texas
and all 50 states under the 10th amendment to the U.S. Constitution.
CONTACT: The Fund to Take Back Texas Prisons, Inc., 1500 So. Dairy
Ashford, Suite 115, Houston, TX 77077.<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=2>Washington Institute For Policy Studies Establishes
Web Site</FONT></B>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Times New Roman">The Washington Institute for
Policy Studies (WIPS) has established a web site on the Internet
at the address: http://www.wips.org. The homepage features an
&quot;Institute Spotlight&quot; which focuses on their latest
publication or event. It will also include: a John Carlson home
page; the latest issues of <I>Counterpoint</I>; listing of staff,
board of directors and board advisors; and a publications and
policy page. CONTACT: Washington Institute for Policy Studies,
P.O. Box 24645, Seattle, WA 98124, 206/938-6300, fax 206/938-6313,
e-mail <a href="mailto:wips@wips.org">wips@wips.org</a>, Internet <a href="http://www.wips.org">http://www.wips.org</a><BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=2>Institute for Justice Publishes Fifth Anniversary
Edition of <I><B>Liberty &amp; Law</B></I></FONT></B>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Times New Roman">The Institute for Justice
has published its fifth anniversary issue of its bimonthly newsletter
<I>Liberty &amp; Law</I>. This issue includes a look back at the
highlights of The Institute for Justice's first five years, inlcuding
profiles of IJ clients in important cases. Also included is a
summary of IJ's school choice agenda. CONTACT: Institute for Justice,
1717 Pennslyvania Avenue, N.W., Suite 200, Washington, D.C. 20006,
202/955-1300, fax 202/955-1329, e-mail <a href="mailto:general@instituteforjustice.org">general@instituteforjustice.org</a>
 Internet <a href="http://www.instituteforjustice.org">http://www.instituteforjustice.org</a><BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=2>Tapes From American Public Philosophy Institute
Conference</FONT></B>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Times New Roman">The American Public Philosophy
Institute is now offering tapes from their June, 1996 conference:
&quot;The Family, Civil Society, and the State.&quot; Conference
speakers included Elizabeth Fox-Genovese, Gertrude Himmelfarb,
David Blankenhorn, Michael Medved, Doug Bandow, Mary Ann Glendon,
Lawrence Criner, Bill Mattox, Hadley Arkes, Marvin Olasky, John
DiIulio, Bill Galston, Bill Kristol, and Bob Casey. CONTACT: American
Public Philosophy Institute, Department of Political Science,
Marquette University, P.O. Box 1881, Milwaukee, WI 53201. <BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=2>Libertad y Desarrollo Establishes Web Site </FONT></B>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Times New Roman">Libertad y Desarrollo, a private
research institution which promotes economic development within
a free social order, is a Chilean think tank commited to free
market ideas and devoted to developing public policies consistent
with free market values. They have established a new web site
on the Internet at the address: http://www.his.com/~ild. CONTACT:
Libertad y Desarrollo, San Crecente 551, Santiago, Chile, 2341894,
fax 2341893, e-mail <a href="mailto:ild@mailnet.rdc.cl">ild@mailnet.rdc.cl</a> Internet <a href="http://www.his.com/~ild">http://www.his.com/~ild</a>
<BR>
