State: Celebrating Private Initiative in Social Services 
San Francisco, CA: May 7 
The Pacific Research Foundation will host its fourth annual privatization awards dinner. The theme will be: 
“Beyond the Welfare State: Celebrating Private Initiative in Social Services.” The dinner will be held on 
Tuesday May 7, 1996 at the Sheraton Palace Hotel in San Francisco and honor the winners of the 
Institute’s 1995 privatization competition. The co-keynote speakers will be the Hon. Curt Pringle, Speaker 
of the California Assembly, and Ms. Eloise Anderson, Director of California Department of Social 
Services. CONTACT: Cindy Sparks, Pacific Research Institute, 755 Sansome Street, San Francisco, CA 
94111, 415/989-0833, fax 415/989-2411. 
