<B>Strengthening Volunteerism Through Wisconsin's
Welfare-Replacement Proposal: A Brief Examination of Time Dollars,
<BR>
</B>by Michael Hartmann
<P>
<I>Report</I>
Vol. 8, No. 10, Wisconsin Policy Research Institute
<P>
Michael Hartmann, Research Fellow at the Wisconsin
Policy Research Institute, examines the current welfare work-requirement
framework, including Wisconsin's new &quot;W-2&quot; welfare-replacement
program. He uses the ideas of  Edgar Cahn and Marvin Olasky, to
introduce the concept of volunteerism. Both Cahn and Olasky believe
that volunteerism is one of the keys to rebuilding the welfare
system and inner city decay. Hartmann concludes that Cahn's concept
of Time Dollars is something that should be used to help bring
people off of welfare rolls and into the workforce and that solutions
to social problems no longer revolve around traditional liberal
or conservative stances, but around new ideas. 35 pp.  CONTACT:
Wisconsin Policy Research Institute, 3107 N. Shepard Ave., Milwaukee,
WI  53211, 414/963-0600, fax 414/963-4230.<BR>
